@startuml fig-dns-custom-server-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Custom DNS Server — UDP Query and Response Flow

participant "debug container\n(dig client)" as C #FFE0B2
participant "dns-server\nPython + dnslib\nUDP :5353" as S #E1BEE7

== Successful Resolution ==

C -> S : UDP datagram\nQuery: A myservice.lab.local?
activate S
S -> S : parse with DNSRecord.parse()\ncheck qname == TARGET_NAME
S -[#43A047]-> C : DNS Reply\nAnswer: A 10.10.10.10\nTTL=30
deactivate S

note right of S
  dnslib constructs a valid
  DNS response with RR record.
end note

|||

== Unknown Domain ==

C -> S : UDP datagram\nQuery: A doesnotexist.local?
activate S
S -> S : parse query\nqname != TARGET_NAME
S -[#FF9800]-> C : DNS Reply\nNo answer records\n(NOERROR, 0 answers)
deactivate S

note right of S
  A valid response with zero
  answer records — not an error,
  simply "no data".
end note

legend right
  The server receives raw UDP bytes,
  parses them into a DNS query object,
  builds a reply and sends it back.
  dnslib handles encoding and decoding
  of the binary DNS wire format.
endlegend
@enduml
